I have a `beforeRouteEnter` in my component that can return a `next(new Error)`, and I have two ways to access this route.

The first is from another component using: 
```javascript
this.$router.push(
    `/route/${id}`,
    complete => {
        // Do somenthing
    },
    error => {
        // Handle Error
    }
);
```

The second is accessing the route direct from the browser, 
 in this case I have only one way to handle the error, with the global `router.onError(error => {})`.

And what I want is, if the error occurs coming from the other component I'll show a message error at the component, and if it occurs coming direct from the browser I want to redirect him to another route.
But the problem is, the global `router.onError(error => {})`  is called  first, so if I redirect him to another route I can't handle the error at my other component, and in the global `onError` I don't even receive at leat a `from` route object.
